Oddworld: Munch's Oddysee is the third game in the Oddworld series. Made in 2001, this HD Revamp is okay at best. At worse, the game is clunky and unamusing. Oddworld is not meant to be a 3-D game in my opinion, and others seem to agree. While this title is certainly catching in terms of cinematics, the gameplay is subpar and the landscapes are as pretty as infected acne. However, the story is nice and the cinematics beautiful, however, good cutscenes don't make game. I do not recommend this.

Rose-tinted glasses aside, this adaptation of the Xbox original release is true to form and during my playthrough so far I haven't (yet) found any glaring omission(s) in gameplay and/or story. Although the on-screen controls and layout customization are quite good, issue(s) can be found. When altered/customized, multiple options buttons, e.g. Motion and Speech buttons, location(s) will revert to their original location(s) when option cycling and will return to their customized location(s) once full cycle of those options has been completed. The camera is a bit difficult to deal with when attempting some of the more difficult action/platform stages as it tends to lag behind the player. The compromises and shortcomings of this adaptation are easily understandable and even remedied, say, should you use a controller instead of the on-screen controls. All in all, the puzzles and the storyline make this port of an already amazing game into an awesome addition to anyone's mobile games library.

replyContent: Hi Bill. Touch anywhere on the left half of the screen to bring up the walking control (virtual analog stick). The stick becomes centered on the first touch point until you release finger. Best to touch in lower left corner so vision is not obscured. If you are left handed you can swap left half of screen with right half in options menu.

content: **Update: Yes please add a disable feature in next release! **Playing this using my earphones and the voice audio and sfx of the characters is all over the place. Depending on where the camera is it'll either come out of the left or right earphone. Never both at the same time. Not sure if this is a bug or "feature", but either way it makes the experience less enjoyable! It's almost the same sensation as having a broken earphone and trying to listen to music.
replyContent: Hi Andy, that's 3D spatial sound which is pretty standard in 3D games. We can add an option to disable this in a future update, no problem. *UPDATE*, Andy, the feature has been implemented and will be available as a toggle in the next update under the sound options.

replyContent: Sorry for your troubles. *UPDATE* We have a workaround to the issue. If you go to Settings - Apps - Munch - Permissions and turn on the toggle for Storage, the game will launch under M. We are working on a more permanent fix for new users.  *EDIT* an update to the app that automates this process is available now.
